Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.120 --> 00:00:06.500
you can make lovely bugs and beetles with
old magazine paper. these bugs have been designed

00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:12.250
by Mr Shastri and demonstrated by Mr Poddar.
take a square of white paper and fold this

00:00:12.250 --> 00:00:18.480
into half. now you just need to make half
of the insect. first its head. there is antennae,

00:00:18.480 --> 00:00:25.480
legs, the main wing, the rear leg and finally
its tail. now with a sharp scissors just cut

00:00:27.620 --> 00:00:34.620
the head, the antennae, the front legs, the
main wing, the rear leg and finally the tail

00:00:53.999 --> 00:01:00.999
of the insect. now by two dots make two eyes
and make your bug stand up. doesn't it look

00:01:06.570 --> 00:01:13.570
pretty? you can shape the legs to make it
more realistic. finally take old magazine

00:01:19.470 --> 00:01:26.470
paper, paper which is tinted which is spots
makes very nice insect. fold this paper into

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:34.200
half and straight away start cutting. first
the head, the antennae, front legs, you can

00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:41.740
see the main wing now. finally the rear legs
and tail. this will be a very beautiful sky

00:01:44.020 --> 00:01:51.020
blue insect with two shining eyes. now you
can make a whole museum of insects, museum

00:01:52.860 --> 00:01:58.460
of natural history using old magazine paper.
some would be bugs, some would be beetles,

00:01:58.460 --> 00:02:04.700
some would be cockroaches. a whole variety
of insects made by sing throw away magazine

00:02:04.700 --> 00:02:08.729
paper. this is very cost effective and very
very pretty.

